<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-05T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="973" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d973">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/258</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-05T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            5, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>247. Your 362, August 13, 6 p.m. This Government has hitherto
                                refrained from any expression of opinion or policy as to the
                                independence of Finland. It therefore deems publication of your
                                statement-inadvisable at present and the Legation at Stockholm has
                                been so informed, adding that as the publication of any appeal from
                                the Finns through us might be construed as intervention in Finnish
                                internal affairs, its publication in that manner at this time
                                appears equally inadvisable.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>